connection?

16:30.796 --> 16:33.530
Who's the you in that question?

16:33.532 --> 16:35.298
Are we in the United States?

16:35.300 --> 16:36.833
There are some people.

16:36.835 --> 16:38.468
Are we in my agency?

16:38.470 --> 16:40.371
Not that I'm aware of.

16:40.373 --> 16:42.874
Am I, personally?

16:42.876 --> 16:45.342
No way.

16:45.344 --> 16:47.377
Okay, the second part
to the question.

16:47.379 --> 16:48.513
No.

16:48.515 --> 16:50.184
Thank you.

16:52.484 --> 16:54.751
So, no one you work with at the
Library of Congress has ever...

16:54.753 --> 16:56.821
found a link between Saddam
Hussein and Al Qaeda?

16:56.823 --> 16:59.524
No one I work with
would expect to find a link.

16:59.526 --> 17:01.324
So, as far as you know...

17:01.326 --> 17:02.793
there's nothing substantial to
tie Iraq to bin Laden?

17:02.795 --> 17:04.461
There's nothing even
circumstantial.

17:04.463 --> 17:06.496
To lump together a secular
leader like Saddam...

17:06.498 --> 17:09.499
with an Islamic extremist
like bin Laden is simply...

17:09.501 --> 17:11.637
to have no understanding
of the Muslim world.

17:15.941 --> 17:17.874
It's a bit timid.

17:17.876 --> 17:19.944
No one's actually come out and
said anything publicly yet.

17:19.945 --> 17:21.945
Maybe it's just backroom
speculation.

17:21.948 --> 17:23.480
Pretty dangerous speculation.

17:23.482 --> 17:25.483
Can't we hit it harder than
this?

17:25.484 --> 17:27.417
The attacks were just 10 days
ago.

17:27.420 --> 17:28.553
Everyone's trying to play
catch-up.

17:28.555 --> 17:30.487
Got to press our reliables.

17:30.489 --> 17:32.489
I'll reach out to The Italian
Lady.

17:32.491 --> 17:34.492
You think you can get Loose
Nukes to go on the record?

17:34.494 --> 17:36.761
I'm lucky to get her on deep
background.

17:36.763 --> 17:40.497
Well, double down on the Charm
Offensive.

17:40.499 --> 17:43.266
<i>Buongiorno,</i> this is Warren
Strobel.

17:43.268 --> 17:46.536
I was looking to get your advice
on a critical scheduling matter.

17:46.538 --> 17:49.607
If you could contact me at your
earliest possible convenience...

17:49.609 --> 17:52.576
I would greatly appreciate it.
Thank you.

17:52.578 --> 17:53.710
<i>Hello.</i>

17:53.712 --> 17:55.513
Yeah, hi, it's Jonathan.

17:55.515 --> 17:56.980
<i>I don't have
anything for you.</i>

17:56.982 --> 18:00.418
No, I know, I know, but I'm
doing a story...

18:00.420 --> 18:02.786
on the administration's seeming
interest in Iraq.

18:02.788 --> 18:04.788
<i>Jonathan, we're
not going to talk about this.</i>

18:04.790 --> 18:07.691
No, I know, I know I'm not
talking about this...

18:07.693 --> 18:10.995
because it's off the record, but
can you give me some indication?

18:10.997 --> 18:12.365
<i>Bye, Jonathan.</i>

18:14.366 --> 18:15.699
What'd she say?

18:15.701 --> 18:18.236
She sends her love.

18:18.238 --> 18:19.637
<i>Across the nation...</i>

18:19.639 --> 18:21.572
<i>flags have been flying off
the shelves.</i>

18:21.574 --> 18:25.476
<i>A wave of patriotism has been
spreading across America.</i>

18:25.478 --> 18:29.280
<i>At times like this,
it's what we do in America.</i>

18:29.282 --> 18:32.682
<i>We the People pull together.</i>

18:32.684 --> 18:34.685
They had a discussion in school
today...

18:34.687 --> 18:37.420
about why America is so great,
right?

18:37.422 --> 18:38.889
Yeah, and what'd you say?

18:38.891 --> 18:40.490
It's a free country.

18:40.492 --> 18:41.926
That's a great answer.

18:41.928 --> 18:43.526
That's Mama's boy.

18:43.528 --> 18:45.295
May I be done now?

18:45.297 --> 18:47.297
Not until I get a big hug.

18:47.299 --> 18:50.400
Okay, after your mom gets a hug.

18:50.402 --> 18:51.971
Oh, whoa!

18:54.673 --> 18:56.306
Proud of you, munchie.

18:56.308 --> 18:58.211
Love you.

19:00.446 --> 19:04.047
They're really pushing this
nationalism thing at school.

19:04.049 --> 19:05.815
What do you expect?

19:05.817 --> 19:07.618
Of course, there's
going to be patriotism now.

19:07.620 --> 19:11.421
Oh, you want to call it
patriotism?

19:11.423 --> 19:12.922
Fine.

19:12.924 --> 19:14.691
It smells a lot like
nationalism to me.

19:14.693 --> 19:19.663
That's how it started in
Yugoslavia before the war.

19:19.665 --> 19:21.634
Tore my country apart.

19:44.957 --> 19:47.891
You want some help?

19:47.893 --> 19:50.529
No, I'm okay, thank you.

19:52.664 --> 19:54.631
Okay, have a good night.

19:54.633 --> 19:55.635
Good night.

20:03.543 --> 20:05.909
How real is the Iraqi
conversation?

20:05.911 --> 20:07.911
There's an argument
taking place.

20:07.913 --> 20:10.848
Yeah? Who's winning it?

20:10.850 --> 20:12.615
I couldn't say.

20:12.617 --> 20:16.853
Look, my boss is gonna send me
to Afghanistan, and all I want..

20:16.855 --> 20:20.390
to know is should he be buying
a roundtrip ticket...

20:20.392 --> 20:24.597
or is Afghanistan just a
layover on the way to Baghdad?

20:28.700 --> 20:31.468
I can't tell you anything.

20:31.470 --> 20:33.504
<i>I believe major acts
of terrorism...</i>

20:33.506 --> 20:36.607
<i>against the U.S. are
state-sponsored.</i>

20:36.609 --> 20:39.810
<i>So, we asked ourselves,
"Who could have been behind...</i>

20:39.812 --> 20:42.746
<i>the most massive terrorist
assault in human history...</i>

20:42.748 --> 20:44.648
<i>"which state?"</i>

20:44.650 --> 20:49.853
<i>I think Iraq is the state that
most immediately comes to mind.</i>

20:49.855 --> 20:52.656
<i>This is an idea which in...</i>

20:52.658 --> 20:54.725
<i>is gaining increased
credibility.</i>

20:54.727 --> 20:56.627
Knight Ridder, it's Strobel.

20:56.629 --> 20:58.094
<i>Jim Woolsey
is going to Europe...</i>

20:58.096 --> 20:59.830
<i>to try to find a link
between Saddam...</i>

20:59.832 --> 21:02.602
<i>and the 1993 World Trade Center
bombing.</i>

21:03.769 --> 21:05.636
Is he freelancing?

21:05.638 --> 21:07.772
<i>He was sent
on an official government jet.</i>

21:07.774 --> 21:10.006
Jesus, who sent him?

21:10.008 --> 21:12.709
<i>The deputy defense secretary.</i>

21:12.711 --> 21:14.911
Can you meet for coffee?

21:14.913 --> 21:16.450
<i>I'll be in touch.</i>

21:17.883 --> 21:19.883
Hi, this is Warren
Strobel with Knight Ridder.

21:19.885 --> 21:21.619
I'm working on a story...

21:21.621 --> 21:23.187
about former CIA director James
Woolsey traveling to Europe.

21:23.189 --> 21:25.188
Do you know anything about that?

21:25.190 --> 21:28.191
<i>I didn't have
anything to do with that.</i>

21:28.193 --> 21:30.194
But you're aware that such
a trip has taken place?

21:30.196 --> 21:33.730
<i>I can't be your only
source on this.</i>

21:33.732 --> 21:35.901
All right, stay in touch.

21:37.702 --> 21:40.470
Hey, John.

21:40.472 --> 21:42.605
Woolsey was sent to Europe
to look for evidence...

21:42.607 --> 21:45.543
linking Saddam to the World
Trade Center bombing in '93.

21:45.545 --> 21:48.711
Wouldn't be a fool's errand if
they didn't send a fool.

21:48.713 --> 21:50.547
This came from The Italian Lady?

21:50.549 --> 21:51.748
And a diplomat who can
confirm...

21:51.750 --> 21:53.082
the trip was arranged by
Wolfowitz.

21:53.084 --> 21:54.752
What the hell is going on
over at Defense?

21:54.754 --> 21:56.786
Question is, are they trying to
figure out...

21:56.788 --> 21:58.555
if there's any truth to their
theory...

21:58.557 --> 22:01.191
or are they already convinced
their theory is true?

22:01.193 --> 22:02.927
You're sure about
this Woolsey trip?

22:02.929 --> 22:04.928
- Positive.
- You have a third source?

22:04.930 --> 22:06.030
- Yeah.
- Who?

22:06.032 --> 22:07.834
Jim Woolsey.

22:20.112 --> 22:23.917
Hey, it's Walcott,
you up for a field trip?

22:26.786 --> 22:28.752
I figured you'd be calling...

22:28.754 --> 22:30.557
I just didn't think
it would be this soon.

22:33.659 --> 22:35.758
How real is the chatter
about Iraq?

22:35.760 --> 22:37.628
Very.

22:37.630 --> 22:41.532
And it's diverting our attention
from the people who attacked us.

22:41.534 --> 22:44.171
How soon before Iraq becomes
the focus?

22:45.904 --> 22:48.639
We need to blow something up.

22:48.641 --> 22:50.674
Not enough targets in
Afghanistan.

22:50.676 --> 22:51.809
What about bin Laden?

22:51.811 --> 22:53.276
You take out bin Laden...

22:53.278 --> 22:55.714
interest in the war goes right
down the shitter.

22:57.650 --> 23:00.851
<i>A joint offensive in
its sixth day in Tora Bora...</i>

23:00.853 --> 23:02.820
<i>bin Laden's suspected
hideout...</i>

23:02.822 --> 23:05.589
<i>but still no signs of the
world's most wanted man.</i>

23:05.591 --> 23:09.159
<i>U.S. B-52s pounding Al Qaeda
positions from the air...</i>

23:09.161 --> 23:10.894
<i>while anti-Taliban tanks...</i>

23:10.896 --> 23:12.696
<i>and troops meet strong
resistance...</i>

23:12.698 --> 23:15.131
<i>cave to cave,
from Al Qaeda fighters.</i>

23:15.133 --> 23:17.001
<i>With yet more conflicting
reports...</i>

23:17.003 --> 23:19.005
<i>on bin Laden's whereabouts.</i>

23:20.940 --> 23:22.672
What you got there...

23:22.674 --> 23:24.675
is that your State of the
Union piece for tomorrow?

23:24.677 --> 23:26.709
- Yup.
- You got a lunch today?

23:26.711 --> 23:28.879
Not with you.

23:28.881 --> 23:30.980
I got a one-on-one with Looney
Tunes over at State.

23:30.982 --> 23:32.582
There's a dry hole.

23:32.584 --> 23:34.284
Yeah, well, I figured if I just
let him ramble on...

23:34.286 --> 23:36.320
he'll accidentally stumble
into something newsworthy.

23:36.322 --> 23:37.755
Yeah, well, give my best.

23:37.757 --> 23:39.790
I will. Hot off the presses,
Beryl.

23:39.792 --> 23:41.225
Did you use punctuation
this time?

23:41.227 --> 23:43.159
I even threw in a few semicolons
just for you.

23:43.161 --> 23:46.764
I bet you're the pride of the
University of Missouri.

23:46.766 --> 23:50.801
<i>Terrorists who once occupied
Afghanistan...</i>

23:50.803 --> 23:53.672
<i>now occupy cells
at Guantanamo Bay.</i>

23:56.909 --> 23:59.976
<i>And terrorist leaders who urged
followers to sacrifice...</i>

23:59.978 --> 24:03.280
<i>their lives are running'
for their own.</i>

24:03.282 --> 24:07.851
Now, the administration's top
priority apart from our own...

24:07.853 --> 24:11.788
security is to ensure
freedom for other countries...

24:11.790 --> 24:16.060
looking to embrace democracy
as a way of life.

24:16.062 --> 24:18.861
Now, we... excuse me... we
understand that we can't...

24:18.863 --> 24:20.863
be the policemen to the world...

24:20.865 --> 24:23.266
but we feel we
have a responsibility to...

24:23.268 --> 24:24.668
Yeah, John Walcott.

24:24.670 --> 24:26.102
<i>John!</i>

24:26.104 --> 24:27.236
Dixie?

24:27.238 --> 24:28.706
<i>John, can you hear me?</i>

24:28.708 --> 24:30.239
Yeah, yeah, I can hear you.

24:30.241 --> 24:32.610
I got a call from one of
our boys downrange today...

24:32.612 --> 24:34.178
asking me what the fuck's
going on.

24:34.180 --> 24:35.979
Are you still in Afghanistan?

24:35.981 --> 24:37.614
Yeah, I'm in Afghanistan...

24:37.616 --> 24:39.115
but nobody knows what the
mission is anymore.

24:39.117 --> 24:41.051
How do you bomb a country back
into the Stone Age...

24:41.053 --> 24:43.219
that's already in the middle
of the goddamn Stone Age?

24:43.221 --> 24:46.357
<i>Our second goal is to prevent
regimes that sponsor terror...</i>

24:46.359 --> 24:50.727
<i>from threatening America,
or our friends and allies...</i>

24:50.729 --> 24:52.630
<i>with weapons of mass
destruction.</i>

24:52.632 --> 24:56.667
We believe that Afghanistan
is ripe for freedom.

24:56.669 --> 25:00.070
Now, this is a country that has
been struggling to free...

25:00.072 --> 25:03.273
<i>itself from the repressive grip
of the Taliban for years.</i>

25:03.275 --> 25:06.643
We've got bin Laden on the run
and they're diverting my assets.

25:06.645 --> 25:08.411
We may never get him in our
crosshairs again.

25:08.413 --> 25:11.982
Whoa, whoa, wait, they're
diverting your assets to where?

25:11.984 --> 25:14.284
<i>Some of these regimes have been
pretty quiet since...</i>

25:14.286 --> 25:18.121
<i>September the 11th, but we know
their true nature.</i>

25:18.123 --> 25:21.958
You know, it's a country in
desperate need of the kind...

25:21.960 --> 25:24.961
of stability that comes with the
rule of law.

25:24.963 --> 25:28.966
<i>North Korea, Iran, Iraq...
states like these...</i>

25:28.968 --> 25:33.871
<i>and their terrorist allies
constitute an axis of evil...</i>

25:33.873 --> 25:35.938
<i>arming to threaten the
peace of the world.</i>

25:35.940 --> 25:37.675
You'll have to excuse me...

25:37.677 --> 25:40.244
Warren, but I have to prepare
a briefing for Secretary Powell.

25:40.246 --> 25:41.245
Sure.

25:41.247 --> 25:42.412
Anything else you need from me?

25:42.414 --> 25:44.180
No, no, thank you.

25:44.182 --> 25:45.983
I think you've given me
more than enough to chew on.

25:45.985 --> 25:47.316
Excellent.

25:47.318 --> 25:48.951
And you feel confident that
Afghanistan...

25:48.953 --> 25:50.286
will accept a Western-style
democracy?

25:50.288 --> 25:51.788
Oh, absolutely.

25:51.790 --> 25:54.291
Just as confident as
we are about Iraq.

25:54.293 --> 25:58.062
Sounds like the debate on Iraq
is getting serious.

25:58.064 --> 26:00.863
Oh, no, no, no, that debate
is over.

26:00.865 --> 26:04.200
Saddam's got to go,
the only question is how.

26:04.202 --> 26:05.369
Good talking to you, Warren.

26:05.371 --> 26:07.273
Yeah, you, too, sir.

26:09.441 --> 26:11.207
The president
is going to invade Iraq.

26:11.209 --> 26:12.942
<i>You got this from Looney Tunes?</i>

26:12.944 --> 26:15.044
Yeah, and confirmed by a
diplomat who says he met...

26:15.046 --> 26:18.148
with Bush, and a foreign leader
recently who came away with...

26:18.150 --> 26:21.485
"The feeling that a decision has
been made to strike Iraq."

26:21.487 --> 26:23.786
Do you think we can get enough
to run the story?

26:23.788 --> 26:25.924
Unfortunately, I do.

26:38.804 --> 26:40.403
So much for the ceasefire.

26:40.405 --> 26:42.206
Yeah, well, really nice of us...

26:42.208 --> 26:44.844
to temporarily stop shooting
at them, though.

26:56.255 --> 26:59.022
♪ I've been bound up
and wound up ♪

26:59.024 --> 27:01.190
♪ Could barely get a sound up ♪

27:01.192 --> 27:02.993
♪ Been cheated mistreated ♪

27:02.995 --> 27:05.763
♪ Don't even want to
think of it ♪

27:05.765 --> 27:07.765
What are you up to, Smucker?

27:07.767 --> 27:11.001
You know, I tried to chat
with your translator today.

27:11.003 --> 27:12.535
Yeah, how'd that go?

27:12.537 --> 27:15.272
Well, for a guy who gets paid
to talk for a living...

27:15.274 --> 27:17.975
he was unusually quiet.

27:17.977 --> 27:20.310
He only talks to me.

27:20.312 --> 27:24.413
Really? And what'd he tell you?

27:24.415 --> 27:27.383
Dollar, I'll let you read
all about it.

27:27.385 --> 27:31.455
Let me see it.

27:31.457 --> 27:35.559
bin Laden's gone, isn't he?

27:35.561 --> 27:39.095
They missed him, didn't they?

27:39.097 --> 27:43.368
He was here and they fucking
missed him!

27:45.403 --> 27:47.236
<i>A senior U.S.
military official...</i>

27:47.238 --> 27:49.473
<i>tells NBC News "Despite the
crushing defeat...</i>

27:49.475 --> 27:51.408
<i>"of Al Qaeda forces
at Tora Bora...</i>

27:51.410 --> 27:54.410
<i>"it's believed now that Osama
bin Laden has slipped...</i>

27:54.412 --> 27:56.947
<i>"across the border into
Pakistan, seeking refuge...</i>

27:56.949 --> 27:58.515
<i>"in a lawless no man's land...</i>

27:58.517 --> 28:01.351
<i>"ruled by renegade tribal
warlords."</i>

28:01.353 --> 28:03.253
Oh, it's official...

28:03.255 --> 28:06.089
this is the saddest event
I've ever attended.

28:06.091 --> 28:08.057
I'm going back to my apartment,
drink a bottle of wine...

28:08.059 --> 28:09.325
and put my head in the oven.

28:09.327 --> 28:11.128
Okay, but before you do that...

28:11.130 --> 28:14.096
I really want you to meet the
guy I was telling you about.

28:14.098 --> 28:16.065
Oh! He just walked in!

28:16.067 --> 28:18.067
Forget the wine, I'll kill
myself now.

28:18.069 --> 28:22.371
No, not him... him.
I'll introduce you.

28:22.373 --> 28:23.506
Pam, please don't.

28:23.508 --> 28:26.409
- Warren! Hey!
- Oh, hi.

28:26.411 --> 28:28.211
Glad you could make it,
come on over.

28:28.213 --> 28:31.582
Warren, this is a
good friend of mine, Lisa Mayr.

28:31.584 --> 28:33.449
Lisa, this is Warren Strobel,
he's a journalist...

28:33.451 --> 28:35.121
and I'm gonna get another drink.

28:37.355 --> 28:39.022
Hi, uh, Lisa?

28:39.024 --> 28:40.457
- Yeah.
- Yeah, nice to meet you.

28:40.459 --> 28:42.128
- Hi.
- Uh...

28:43.461 --> 28:46.463
Did you ever make it
into your apartment?

28:46.465 --> 28:50.967
Uh, oh, yeah, yeah, yeah,
no, no, no, I'm sorry.

28:50.969 --> 28:54.406
- Yeah, I made it in okay.
- Good. Good.

28:56.141 --> 28:58.274
So, you're a journalist?

28:58.276 --> 29:01.143
Yeah, yeah, for Knight Ridder.

29:01.145 --> 29:03.947
Oh, is that a magazine
or a newspaper?

29:03.949 --> 29:09.052
It's actually a consortium
of 31 newspapers, actually.

29:09.054 --> 29:10.586
Well, my stories go out to all
of our newspapers...

29:10.588 --> 29:14.091
and each one has the option
to publish or not.

29:14.093 --> 29:17.127
Oh, okay. I've always wondered
how that worked.

29:17.129 --> 29:18.430
Yeah.

29:21.600 --> 29:25.669
Hey, I got married when
I was 22.

29:25.671 --> 29:29.339
And we're only recently
separated, so...

29:29.341 --> 29:31.941
This is a little awkward for me.

29:31.943 --> 29:33.310
It's okay.

29:33.312 --> 29:35.245
I'm a little out of practice.

29:35.247 --> 29:39.082
Why don't you start
by asking me a question?

29:39.084 --> 29:41.854
Sure, yeah.

29:43.655 --> 29:45.924
Are you a Republican
or a Democrat?

29:47.426 --> 29:49.258
Try again.

29:49.260 --> 29:52.295
Yeah, of course, she wants you
to call her.

29:52.297 --> 29:54.031
She gave you her card.

29:54.033 --> 29:56.166
No, maybe she's just trying
to gin up business.

29:56.168 --> 29:58.669
At a singles mixer
on Valentine's Day?

29:58.671 --> 30:00.938
What? So, call her? I should
call her?

30:00.940 --> 30:02.973
What? No, no, no,
actually, let her dangle.

30:02.975 --> 30:04.941
There's nothing a woman in her
30s likes more...

30:04.943 --> 30:07.177
than a guy who takes his time.

30:07.179 --> 30:09.012
I'm fine, Arthur, I'm fine.

30:09.014 --> 30:11.480
It's just that I'm getting a
little tired...

30:11.482 --> 30:13.417
of picking up your paper
every morning...

30:13.419 --> 30:15.384
and seeing that you're not
running our stories.

30:15.386 --> 30:17.219
I mean, last time I looked...

30:17.221 --> 30:21.057
The Philadelphia Inquirer was
a Knight Ridder paper, right?

30:21.059 --> 30:24.961
The point is, there's no point
in being a Knight Ridder paper..

30:24.963 --> 30:26.697
if you're not going to run
Knight Ridder stories.

30:26.699 --> 30:28.732
John, we've been through
this already.

30:28.734 --> 30:30.434
Your stories don't fit...

30:30.436 --> 30:33.269
in with what we're doing
over here right now.

30:33.271 --> 30:35.371
Don't fit? Don't fit with what?
The truth?

30:35.373 --> 30:37.274
<i>What's the matter, Arthur...</i>

30:37.276 --> 30:39.008
