learn, son.

47:07.198 --> 47:08.667
Landay.

47:11.368 --> 47:14.469
- It's Joe Galloway.
- Wow.

47:14.471 --> 47:16.605
Man even walks like he has
a Bronze Star.

47:16.607 --> 47:17.973
<i>Hello.</i>

47:17.975 --> 47:20.275
Oh, hi, yeah, it's Landay.

47:20.277 --> 47:21.576
<i>Hello, Jonathan.</i>

47:21.578 --> 47:27.382
Hi. Crazy weather we're having,
huh?

47:27.384 --> 47:29.417
<i>You're calling me to chat
about the weather?</i>

47:29.419 --> 47:34.056
No, no, yeah. Actually, I wanted
to ask you about WMD.

47:34.058 --> 47:35.623
It'll be deep, deep background.

47:35.625 --> 47:37.292
<i>Goodbye, Jonathan.</i>

47:37.294 --> 47:40.228
No wait, don't hang up.

47:40.230 --> 47:44.199
That Charm Offensive...
that's formidable.

47:44.201 --> 47:48.471
Listen, we need you here.

47:48.473 --> 47:51.172
You've developed sources over
the years that have access...

47:51.174 --> 47:54.210
that Landay and Strobel
just can't get.

47:54.212 --> 47:55.611
I'll make it easy on you.

47:55.613 --> 47:57.413
I'll give you a column...

47:57.415 --> 48:01.449
and your name doesn't have to
appear on anything else.

48:01.451 --> 48:04.286
Whatever else you want to write
on the side, you can...

48:04.288 --> 48:06.554
and of course, there won't be
any glory, but...

48:06.556 --> 48:08.727
Glory's for young men.

48:11.361 --> 48:13.462
Let me percolate on it.

48:13.464 --> 48:15.531
<i>Let me turn to the issue
of Iraq.</i>

48:15.533 --> 48:18.567
<i>You have said that it poses...</i>

48:18.569 --> 48:20.803
<i>a mortal threat to the
United States.</i>

48:20.805 --> 48:24.406
<i>How? Define "mortal threat."</i>

48:24.408 --> 48:29.210
<i>Well, this'll take some time,
but it's important for us...</i>

48:29.212 --> 48:31.112
<i>as I mentioned earlier...</i>

48:31.114 --> 48:34.049
<i>to remember that the world
has changed, that prior to...</i>

48:34.051 --> 48:35.784
I'd forgotten the world
had changed.

48:35.786 --> 48:37.719
So did I. I'm so happy he
mentioned that.

48:37.721 --> 48:41.357
<i>What, specifically, has he
obtained that you believe...</i>

48:41.359 --> 48:43.792
<i>would enhance his nuclear
development program?</i>

48:43.794 --> 48:45.828
<i>Well, in the nuclear weapons
arena...</i>

48:45.830 --> 48:48.630
<i>you've got specifically
aluminum tubes.</i>

48:48.632 --> 48:50.399
<i>There's a story in The New York
Times this morning...</i>

48:50.401 --> 48:53.502
<i>this is and I want to attribute
to The Times.</i>

48:53.504 --> 48:55.437
<i>I don't want to talk about,
obviously...</i>

48:55.439 --> 48:58.607
<i>specific intelligence sources,
but it's now public that...</i>

48:58.609 --> 49:03.645
<i>in fact he has been seeking to
acquire, and we have been...</i>

49:03.647 --> 49:06.449
<i>able to intercept and prevent
him from acquiring...</i>

49:06.451 --> 49:08.150
<i>through this particular
channel...</i>

49:08.152 --> 49:10.286
<i>the kinds of tubes that are
necessary...</i>

49:10.288 --> 49:12.087
<i>to build a centrifuge.</i>

49:12.089 --> 49:15.123
<i>And the centrifuge is required
to take low-grade uranium...</i>

49:15.125 --> 49:18.560
<i>and enhance it into highly
enriched uranium...</i>

49:18.562 --> 49:21.330
<i>which is what you have to have
in order to build a bomb.</i>

49:21.332 --> 49:23.866
Lucky for him, someone leaked
that to The Times.

49:23.868 --> 49:27.169
Avoids the pesky nuisance
of being arrested...

49:27.171 --> 49:28.804
for revealing classified
information.

49:28.806 --> 49:30.839
One can only wonder how Judy
Miller and Michael Gordon...

49:30.841 --> 49:31.873
got that information.

49:31.875 --> 49:35.578
<i>Does it bother you, bug you...</i>

49:35.580 --> 49:38.714
<i>that you have not captured
Osama bin Laden in over a year?</i>

49:38.716 --> 49:45.453
<i>I'd like to see him on
television in handcuffs...</i>

49:45.455 --> 49:47.489
<i>if I can put it
into those terms.</i>

49:47.491 --> 49:49.458
<i>I think all of us would.</i>

49:49.460 --> 49:53.228
<i>But I don't lay awake at night
concerned about that.</i>

49:53.230 --> 49:55.563
<i>There's one school of thought
that says he's already dead.</i>

49:55.565 --> 49:57.165
<i>We haven't heard anything
of him in many months.</i>

49:57.167 --> 49:58.533
<i>What do you think?</i>

49:58.535 --> 49:59.634
<i>I don't know, I really
don't know.</i>

49:59.636 --> 50:01.569
<i>I can argue it round or flat.</i>

50:01.571 --> 50:04.172
I didn't know we were still
debating the shape of the earth.

50:04.174 --> 50:06.143
I've got sources on both sides.

50:08.212 --> 50:10.645
<i>But the U.S. military would be
enormously effective...</i>

50:10.647 --> 50:12.515
<i>in this circumstance.</i>

50:12.517 --> 50:15.451
<i>And I don't think it would be
that tough a fight.</i>

50:15.453 --> 50:17.386
<i>That is, I don't think there's
any question...</i>

50:17.388 --> 50:19.221
<i>that we would prevail and we
would achieve our objective.</i>

50:19.223 --> 50:21.656
Landay.

50:21.658 --> 50:24.292
Yeah?

50:24.294 --> 50:26.630
We are right, aren't we?

50:28.866 --> 50:30.835
Everybody, listen up.

50:34.839 --> 50:36.808
We're not NBC.

50:38.276 --> 50:40.341
We're not ABC. We're not CBS.

50:40.343 --> 50:43.347
We're not FOX. We're not CNN.

50:44.482 --> 50:46.582
We're not The New York Times.

50:46.584 --> 50:48.553
We're not The Washington Post.

50:50.453 --> 50:52.423
We are Knight Ridder.

50:56.527 --> 51:02.598
We have readers who live in
towns with military bases.

51:02.600 --> 51:06.335
Fort Benning, Fort Bragg,
Fort Jackson...

51:06.337 --> 51:12.674
and over 40 other military bases
throughout this country.

51:12.676 --> 51:17.446
If every other news organization
wants to be stenographers...

51:17.448 --> 51:20.518
for the Bush administration,
let them.

51:22.786 --> 51:26.658
We don't write for people who
send other people's kids to war.

51:28.725 --> 51:33.198
We write for people
whose kids get sent to war.

51:35.866 --> 51:38.333
So, when the government
says something...

51:38.335 --> 51:40.839
you only have one question
to ask.

51:44.341 --> 51:46.277
Is it true?

51:52.450 --> 51:54.386
I'm through percolating.

51:57.488 --> 51:59.420
Let's get to work.

51:59.422 --> 52:01.690
Administration officials spanned
out on the Sunday talk shows...

52:01.692 --> 52:03.926
to make the case for an invasion
of Iraq.

52:03.928 --> 52:06.895
Who else is involved in
The Office of Special Planning?

52:06.897 --> 52:10.598
Wolfowitz, Feith, couple others.

52:10.600 --> 52:12.967
Instead of listening to people
who have spent their careers...

52:12.969 --> 52:16.804
evaluating threats, they're
streaming questionable intel...

52:16.806 --> 52:18.707
from unreliable sources and
taking it...

52:18.709 --> 52:20.509
directly to the White House.

52:20.511 --> 52:22.745
<i>George Tenet, Director
of Central Intelligence...</i>

52:22.747 --> 52:25.346
<i>told Senators, he could not
rule out cooperation...</i>

52:25.348 --> 52:26.617
<i>between Osama bin Laden
and Al Qaeda.</i>

52:29.386 --> 52:31.587
I've seen the specs on those
aluminum tubes.

52:31.589 --> 52:33.621
They're too small to be used
for enriching uranium.

52:33.623 --> 52:35.024
What does that mean?

52:35.026 --> 52:36.792
They can't be used
for a nuclear bomb.

52:36.794 --> 52:38.594
<i>The President
of the United States...</i>

52:38.596 --> 52:39.928
<i>said we're not going to permit
nations to develop...</i>

52:39.930 --> 52:41.897
<i>weapons of mass destruction...</i>

52:41.899 --> 52:43.699
<i>as they're gonna supply those
weapons to a network...</i>

52:43.701 --> 52:45.366
<i>of terrorism that could attack
the United States.</i>

52:45.368 --> 52:47.870
Cheney is trying to shut
out Powell.

52:47.872 --> 52:49.471
Where'd you get this stuff?

52:49.473 --> 52:51.339
Old friend.

52:51.341 --> 52:53.375
<i>We're starting to
see a consensus from within...</i>

52:53.377 --> 52:55.377
<i>the administration for the
removal of Saddam Hussein.</i>

52:55.379 --> 52:57.379
<i>The
administration has pointed...</i>

52:57.381 --> 52:59.681
<i>to a secret meeting in Prague
between Iraqi intelligence...</i>

52:59.683 --> 53:01.449
<i>and 9/11 hijacker,
Mohamed Atta.</i>

53:01.451 --> 53:03.419
<i>Bush administration is pressing
the United Nations...</i>

53:03.421 --> 53:05.554
<i>Security Council for
a resolution...</i>

53:05.556 --> 53:07.455
<i>to put pressure on Iraq.</i>

53:07.457 --> 53:09.424
<i>President Bush will address
the United Nations today...</i>

53:09.426 --> 53:11.759
<i>in hopes of putting together
a multi-national coalition...</i>

53:11.761 --> 53:13.594
<i>to disarm Saddam Hussein.</i>

53:13.596 --> 53:15.698
<i>The White House is lobbying
Congress to authorize...</i>

53:15.700 --> 53:17.799
<i>the use of force in Iraq.</i>

53:17.801 --> 53:19.868
The minute these guys get
their hands on anything...

53:19.870 --> 53:21.536
remotely resembling evidence...

53:21.538 --> 53:23.471
they leak it to
The New York Times.

53:23.473 --> 53:24.873
Now, I understand the position
you're in...

53:24.875 --> 53:27.509
but please don't hang up on me.

53:27.511 --> 53:28.976
<i>Okay.</i>

53:28.978 --> 53:32.547
Okay, the vice president
of the United States...

53:32.549 --> 53:35.984
went to the V.F.W. and said that
Saddam Hussein...

53:35.986 --> 53:38.953
is on the threshold of
developing a nuclear weapon.

53:38.955 --> 53:41.556
Then he goes on national
television...

53:41.558 --> 53:42.790
and says the same thing.

53:42.792 --> 53:46.060
<i>Your question?</i>

53:46.062 --> 53:49.498
Ask the question.

53:49.500 --> 53:52.533
What I want to know is,
is Dick Cheney ignoring...

53:52.535 --> 53:55.103
good intelligence that
contradicts his assumptions...

53:55.105 --> 53:59.074
or is he just getting bad
intelligence?

53:59.076 --> 54:02.681
<i>The vice president is lying.</i>

54:04.881 --> 54:06.781
Thank you, thank you so much.

54:06.783 --> 54:09.051
What? What, what, what?
What'd she say?

54:09.053 --> 54:10.786
He's lying.

54:10.788 --> 54:12.788
- He's lying.
- Cheney is lying.

54:12.790 --> 54:14.989
- Cheney's lying!
- Cheney's lying!

54:14.991 --> 54:17.525
- He's lying! John!
- He's lying!

54:17.527 --> 54:19.627
John!

54:19.629 --> 54:20.862
Where the hell is he?

54:20.864 --> 54:22.531
Here we go. Here we go.

54:22.533 --> 54:24.466
- He's lying.
- He's lying.

54:24.468 --> 54:26.435
Cheney's lying.

54:26.437 --> 54:27.870
Where did this come from?

54:27.872 --> 54:29.538
Loose Nukes.

54:29.540 --> 54:31.440
Okay.

54:31.442 --> 54:33.808
Now, we know what's being talk
about, we got to get inside...

54:33.810 --> 54:36.812
those meetings and find out if
there's a dissenting opinion.

54:36.814 --> 54:38.614
I may have a guy.

54:38.616 --> 54:40.047
Anybody we know?

54:40.049 --> 54:41.652
The Usual Suspect.

54:52.897 --> 54:54.862
You didn't want to do
this in a parking garage?

54:54.864 --> 54:57.498
If there was one that served
Pad Thai, I would.

54:57.500 --> 54:59.902
How's civilian life?

54:59.904 --> 55:02.504
My retirement lasted about
four hours.

55:02.506 --> 55:04.205
You're with Knight Ridder?

55:04.207 --> 55:06.574
I don't even have a desk yet.
How the hell do you know that?

55:06.576 --> 55:08.076
I have my ways.

55:08.078 --> 55:09.944
You been following what we're
doing over there?

55:09.946 --> 55:11.179
Yes, I have.

55:11.181 --> 55:12.681
And?

55:12.683 --> 55:14.449
You two may be singlehandedly
saving...

55:14.451 --> 55:17.553
the Fourth Estate from
extinction.

55:17.555 --> 55:20.221
Mainstream media hasn't picked
up a thing we been running.

55:20.223 --> 55:21.857
Should be all the confirmation
you need...

55:21.859 --> 55:23.094
that you're onto something.

55:26.062 --> 55:28.696
What can I do for you?

55:28.698 --> 55:30.732
We need some help with the
higher ups.

55:30.734 --> 55:31.732
How high?

55:31.734 --> 55:33.469
High as you can get us.

55:33.471 --> 55:35.170
You've been around a long time,
Joe.

55:35.172 --> 55:37.672
I doubt there's anything there
that'll surprise you.

55:37.674 --> 55:39.475
I was married one time
to a woman who thought...

55:39.477 --> 55:41.643
New Hampshire was the capital
of Massachusetts.

55:41.645 --> 55:44.612
There's always something you
don't see coming.

55:44.614 --> 55:47.949
What do you want to know?

55:47.951 --> 55:51.053
Everything the administration
doesn't want us to know.

55:51.055 --> 55:54.459
You and I are going to be eating
a lot of Pad Thai.

55:59.497 --> 56:01.496
What kind of time frame
are we looking at?

56:01.498 --> 56:02.897
Next month, Congress
is scheduled to vote...

56:02.899 --> 56:04.165
on whether or not to give
the president...

56:04.167 --> 56:05.868
the authorization to go to war.

56:05.870 --> 56:06.935
Are the votes there?

56:06.937 --> 56:08.603
The administration thinks so.

56:08.605 --> 56:14.009
Mr. President, 38 years ago,
I, Robert C. Byrd...

56:14.011 --> 56:17.612
voted on the Tonkin Gulf
Resolution.

56:17.614 --> 56:21.149
The resolution that authorized
the president to use military...

56:21.151 --> 56:23.150
force to repel armed attacks...

56:23.152 --> 56:27.589
and to prevent further communist
aggression in Southeast Asia.

56:27.591 --> 56:31.225
A joint resolution to authorize
the use of United States...

56:31.227 --> 56:34.730
armed forces against Iraq should
be brought to a close.

56:34.732 --> 56:36.931
The clerk will call the roll.

56:36.933 --> 56:39.134
<i>Mr. Biden, aye.</i>

56:39.136 --> 56:41.169
<i>Mrs. Clinton, aye.</i>

56:41.171 --> 56:43.638
It was this resolution that
provided the basis...

56:43.640 --> 56:47.542
for American involvement
in the war in Vietnam.

56:47.544 --> 56:49.877
<i>Mr. Kerry, aye.</i>

56:49.879 --> 56:52.047
<i>Mr. Lieberman, aye.</i>

56:52.049 --> 56:54.016
<i>Mr. Lott, aye.</i>

56:54.018 --> 56:55.951
It was this resolution...

56:55.953 --> 57:00.989
that lead to the deaths
of 58,000 Americans.

57:00.991 --> 57:03.324
<i>Mr. McCain, aye.</i>

57:03.326 --> 57:05.560
<i>Mr. McConnell, aye.</i>

57:05.562 --> 57:10.699
After all that carnage, we began
to learn that in voting...

57:10.701 --> 57:12.768
for the Tonkin Gulf
resolution...

57:12.770 --> 57:15.904
we were basing our votes
on bad information.

57:15.906 --> 57:18.172
And history is repeating itself.

57:18.174 --> 57:20.308
<i>Mr. Santorum, aye.</i>

57:20.310 --> 57:23.679
I urge senators to go down
on the Capital Mall...

57:23.681 --> 57:26.181
and look at the Vietnam
Memorial.

57:26.183 --> 57:29.250
Nearly every day, you will find
someone at that wall...

57:29.252 --> 57:31.587
weeping for a loved one.

57:31.589 --> 57:33.654
<i>Mr. Sessions, aye.</i>

57:33.656 --> 57:36.158
I will always remember the words
of Senator Wayne Morse.

57:36.160 --> 57:38.627
<i>Mr. Specter, aye.</i>

57:38.629 --> 57:40.895
He stated, "The resolution will
pass and senators...

57:40.897 --> 57:44.632
"who vote for it will live
to regret it."

57:44.634 --> 57:46.667
We got K-10, we got Dixie,
we don't need another source.

57:46.669 --> 57:48.270
You know we got this.

57:48.272 --> 57:50.237
Look, when you're accusing the
secretary of defense...

57:50.239 --> 57:52.107
of running a shadow
intelligence unit...

57:52.109 --> 57:54.676
out of the Pentagon, it's nice
to have a little insurance.

57:54.678 --> 57:55.913
That's all I'm saying.

57:59.984 --> 58:02.350
All right, let's share it
with the rest of the class.

58:02.352 --> 58:04.085
You want to tell them?

58:04.087 --> 58:07.723
Earlier today, I was summoned
to the Pentagon.

58:07.725 --> 58:09.056
By whom?

58:09.058 --> 58:12.127
Rumsfeld, Ol' Limp Dick
sent a message saying...

58:12.129 --> 58:13.929
"All your sources are retired
generals."

58:13.931 --> 58:15.864
And I said, "All due respect,
sir...

58:15.866 --> 58:18.799
"80% of my sources are
active military."

58:18.801 --> 58:20.636
"Some of them are working
in this building...

58:20.638 --> 58:22.837
"and some of them are actually
working on your staff."

58:22.839 --> 58:25.806
"And hell, one or two of them
might even be in this room."

58:25.808 --> 58:27.942
Did you actually have sources
in the room?

58:27.944 --> 58:31.082
No, but it was fun watching him
sweat like whores in church.

58:33.817 --> 58:35.783
How close are we to getting
something we can run with

58:35.785 --> 58:37.185
on the Office of Special Plans?

58:37.187 --> 58:39.020
Well, we already got...

58:39.022 --> 58:41.656
No, we're just gonna check
with a couple more sources.

58:41.658 --> 58:43.658
What's wrong with the sources
you have?

58:43.660 --> 58:46.094
Well, we just want to be
certain.

58:46.096 --> 58:49.096
You know, you sit on a story
like this, the dam bursts.

58:49.098 --> 58:51.001
Let's just move on this,
okay, boys?

58:54.904 --> 58:56.237
When are you gonna be finished?

58:56.239 --> 59:00.243
Just a few more minutes, baby.

59:02.846 --> 59:06.781
I can't sleep with the computer
light on.

59:06.783 --> 59:09.219
Actually, I'm done.

59:13.690 --> 59:17.025
So, what are you working on?

59:17.027 --> 59:19.828
Rumsfeld has a secret Intel
group that's going...

59:19.830 --> 59:24.835
around the CIA to manufacture
a case for war.

59:29.239 --> 59:31.440
What the fuck, Jonathan?

59:31.442 --> 59:33.107
What?

59:33.109 --> 59:35.078
Have you been talking about this
on the phone?

59:37.281 --> 59:38.779
Yeah, of course.

59:38.781 --> 59:40.651
So, what?

59:43.187 --> 59:47.188
- They will hear you.
- Vlatka.

59:47.190 --> 59:49.824
You're writing about infighting
between spy agencies.

59:49.826 --> 59:50.926
So?

59:50.928 --> 59:53.328
They're spy agencies, Jonathan.

59:53.330 --> 59:55.964
They listen to your calls,
they read your emails.

59:55.966 --> 59:57.966
They probably bugged this house.

59:57.968 --> 59:59.967
You're being paranoid.

59:59.969 --> 01:00:01.335
You're being naive.

01:00:01.337 --> 01:00:04.739
This isn't Yugoslavia,
this is America.

01:00:04.741 --> 01:00:07.007
America has changed.

01:00:07.009 --> 01:00:08.375
War is big business for them.

01:00:08.377 --> 01:00:11.045
You get in their way,
they're gonna kill you.

01:00:11.047 --> 01:00:15.817
Honey, you are being ridiculous.
All right? Come on.

01:00:15.819 --> 01:00:19.054
Don't you get it?

01:00:19.056 --> 01:00:21.890
You know what these people
are capable of?

01:00:21.892 --> 01:00:24.493
You have a family!

01:00:24.495 --> 01:00:28.098
Vlatka. Vlatka!

01:00:32.902 --> 01:00:37.239
Oh, somebody's struggling.
What's the matter?

01:00:37.241 --> 01:00:40.542
Oh, Vlatka kept me up all night.

01:00:40.544 --> 01:00:42.176
All right!

01:00:42.178 --> 01:00:46.047
No, not that like that. It was
conspiracy theories.

01:00:46.049 --> 01:00:47.415
About what?

01:00:47.417 --> 01:00:50.951
Oh... she thinks the government
is monitoring us.

01:00:50.953 --> 01:00:54.124
I mean, it's ridiculous.

01:00:56.225 --> 01:00:57.761
Check your email.

01:01:09.906 --> 01:01:11.839
John, you got to see this.

01:01:11.841 --> 01:01:14.042
Oh, hold on a second.

01:01:14.044 --> 01:01:17.248
Arthur, I really don't want to
have this conversation again.

01:01:19.382 --> 01:01:22.819
He hung up. What is it?

01:01:30.060 --> 01:01:31.362
What do we do?

01:01:50.080 --> 01:01:52.047
- You're such a wuss.
- You're a wuss.

